{
  "stem": "24268.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And just before the war, we'd started-- anti-Semitism-- after the Marshall [INAUDIBLE] passed away, anti-Semitism started to grow and came more to the surface.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they start to-- their slogans, anti-Semitic slogans, and boycotting, boycotting, boycotting the Jewish stores, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my sister was standing, matter of fact, by-- not far from this store, on this street, on her skates.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And a Pole-- she slipped and fell down.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And a Pole passing to work-- he just deliberately stepped on her leg and broke her leg.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then my parents started to like to sell the home and try to emigrate, but it was too much already pressure, that they knew that we wouldn't be able to sell the house.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "If they did want it, probably for nothing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So it was difficult.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] what can I say?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think I have picture what I mentioned to you, when I was in Israel, visiting somebody had-- a friend of mine, which she was-- I was very surprised that she was willing to-- I think, give up her picture and give it to me.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She brought it to me and just reminisce, and to show the teachers we had, and the whole gang, the class which we participated together.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So-- Before the war, you know, when you were still a little girl, and, you know, 10, 11, 12 years old, tell me what Sosnowiec was like?",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Sosnowiec--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--was a great community.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we actually lived in the suburb, [?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Shelsa. ?] This is a little bit-- it was more-- it's a mixed-- actually Jewish and Polish, mixed-- what do you call?",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Can you help me out?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "A mixed--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, a community, right.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were-- but a lot of business people [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
